> <ChEBI ID>
CHEBI:421707

> <ChEBI NAME>
abacavir

> <STAR>
3

> <DEFINITION>
A 2,6-diaminopurine that is (1<i>S</i>)-cyclopent-2-en-1-ylmethanol in which the <em>pro</em>-<i>R</i> hydrogen at the 4-position is substituted by a 2-amino-6-(cyclopropylamino)-9<em>H</em>-purin-9-yl group. A nucleoside analogue reverse transcriptase inhibitor (NRTI) with antiretroviral activity against HIV, it is used (particularly as the sulfate) with other antiretrovirals in combination therapy of HIV infection.

